# Teaching: spoke-bootstrap-zai-github-config-v1
**Source:** hub
**Session:** gardener-2026-04-07
**Created:** 2026-04-07T00:00:00Z
**Impact:** 7

## What changed and why it matters

When a new spoke is created it needs two pieces of config to operate autonomously:

1. **z.ai API** — the low-cost model endpoint used for teaching adoption (Pass 1) and lug execution (Pass 2). Without this, spokes fall back to Claude or fail silently.
2. **GitHub SSH identity** — all spokes use SSH remotes (`git@github.com:mariov96/{repo}.git`). Without correct git config, commits fail.

Previously, each new spoke had to be told this manually. This teaching documents the canonical config so the gardener can distribute it automatically.

## Migration instructions

### 1. z.ai API config

Create or update `.env.dev` in the spoke root:

```bash
# .env.dev
ZAI_API_KEY=<your-key-here>   # per-user, never committed
```

The z.ai endpoint and models are fixed — no per-spoke config needed:

| Purpose | Model |
|---------|-------|
| Teaching adoption (Pass 1, Haiku-tier) | `glm-4.5-air` |
| Lug execution (Pass 2, full-tier) | `glm-4.5` |
| Endpoint | `https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4/chat/completions` |

> **Discovery note:** The correct path is `/api/coding/paas/v4` — NOT `/api/paas/v4` (returns 404).

Add to `WAI-State.json` under `context.integrations`:

```json
"zai": {
  "endpoint": "https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4/chat/completions",
  "model_teaching_adoption": "glm-4.5-air",
  "model_lug_execution": "glm-4.5",
  "auth": "Bearer $ZAI_API_KEY (from .env.dev — never committed)"
}
```

### 2. GitHub SSH config

Verify local git config is set:

```bash
git config user.name   # should be: mariov96
git config user.email  # should be: mariov96@gmail.com
```

If missing, set project-level config:

```bash
git config user.name "mariov96"
git config user.email "mariov96@gmail.com"
```

SSH key is at `~/.ssh` (host-configured — no per-spoke action needed).

All spoke repos use SSH remotes:

```bash
git remote -v
# origin  git@github.com:mariov96/{spoke-repo}.git (fetch)
# origin  git@github.com:mariov96/{spoke-repo}.git (push)
```

If the remote is HTTPS, convert to SSH:

```bash
git remote set-url origin git@github.com:mariov96/{spoke-repo}.git
```

## Prerequisites

```bash
# Verify SSH key is available
ls ~/.ssh/id_* 2>/dev/null && echo "SSH key present" || echo "MISSING: configure SSH key"
# Verify ZAI_API_KEY env var is set or in .env.dev
[ -f .env.dev ] && grep -q ZAI_API_KEY .env.dev && echo "zai configured" || echo "MISSING: add ZAI_API_KEY to .env.dev"
```

## Batch Sequence

- **Apply order:** 1 (bootstrap — apply before any lug execution)
- **Depends on:** None
- **Parallel-safe:** yes

## safe_to_auto_adopt: true

Config values are non-destructive and additive. Gardener can distribute to all spokes.
